<Figure Size: (1500 x 800)>

The graph above shows median home prices and average sales of Haas avocados over time between 2015 - 2020. Over time, median home prices increase by hundreds of thousands for all cities. However, the average sales of avocados stay relatively the same respectively for each city, with a possible exception to LA. This possible increase in avocado sales in LA could be when avocado toast became increasingly popular from social media. From this plot, we can see that houses are getting more and more expensive, which means they are become less affordable for most people. Yet, the prices of avocados and their sales stay relatively the same. It may not the avocado toast causing millenials to be unable to afford a house, but the increasing prices in homes. More statistical analyses are needed to test this hypotheses, with the inclusion in other factors such as average salary per person per city. In general, however, people are unable to afford to buy a home because home prices are increasing.
